addProposal(string).details: Only voters can execute this function, not the owner. It raises a "ProposalRegistered" event.

params._desc: Represents the description of the proposal as a String

addVoter(address).details: Only the owner can execute this function, which raises a "VoterRegistered" event

params._addr: The address of the voter to be registered

getWinningProposal().details: The workflowStatus needs to be set to "VotesTallied" for the function to execute

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setVote(uint128).details: Only voters can execute this function. Voterc can only vote once. The function also calculates after each votes which proposal is winning.

params._id: The id of the psoposal for which the voter decides to vote

startProposalsRegistering().details: Only the owner can execute these. They are used to organize the vote by restricting some functions use ans allowing others

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
